Package org.thedryden.workmanager

Class LoggingTemplate

java.lang.Object
org.thedryden.workmanager.LoggingTemplate
public class LoggingTemplate
extends java.lang.Object
The purpose of this package is to allow you to customize how the logging messages and their levels. You will be able to change both the contents of the message and the logging level of the message, but you will not be able to change the variables passed to that message, or the order those variables appear. For each message the variable that will be passed into that message will be listed in the description of the setter. This class contains a collection of static values. Since these values are all static, a change to any of the values will change how logging works for the all uses of this package.
Author:
Matthew Dryden
